What you need to know:

Kyrie Irving tallied 15 points and 11 rebounds and Landry Shamet and Tyler Johnson scored 17 and 15 points respectively off the bench for the Nets, who won despite missing all-star James HardenThe Philadelphia 76ers kept pace with the Nets for the number one seed in the standings, wrapping up their six-game road swing on a winning note by beating the Cleveland Cavaliers 114-94Trae Young scored 15 of his 28 points in the two overtime periods as the Atlanta Hawks outlasted the San Antonio Spurs 134-129 in a double-overtime thrillerJeff Green, Brooklyn Nets, Kyrie Irving, Charlotte Hornets, NBA, Philadelphia 76ers, Cleveland Cavaliers, Atlanta Hawks, San Antonio Spurs, Denver Nuggets, Los Angeles Clippers